					<head>Avicenna&apos;s Kanon (Book III)</head>
					<msContents rend="visible">
						<summary>Book III of Avicenna's Canon in Hebrew translation</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n83733838">
							<locus from="1r" to="259v"/>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/89770781">Avicenna, 980-1037</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/89770781">אבן סינא, אלחסין בן עבדאללה</persName>
							</author>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḳanon (Sefer 3)</title>
							<title xml:lang="he"> קאנון (ספר ג’)</title>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">
								<locus n="243v"/> תם ונשלם שבח לבורא עולם יי ברוך נותן ליעף כח ... סליק להו הספר סזה מהרפואות והוא הספר השלישי לאבן סיני הרופא בסייעתא דשמיא התהלה לאל תומך וסומך כל נופל וזורף חלש ורפה... </colophon>
							<note>
								<p>The words הספר השלישי מספר הקאנון have not been filled in at the beginning.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of approximately the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment</support>
								<extent rend="visible">[iii]+243+[iii] <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>309</height>
										<width>221</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>207</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>259 folios (+3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end of the manuscript). Parallel Hebrew foliation begins on fol. 2 (fol. א)</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>25 quires: i<hi rend="sup">9+1</hi> ii-xxiii<hi rend="sup">10</hi> xxiv<hi rend="sup">8</hi>, xxv<hi rend="sup">8-3</hi>.</p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires.</p>
									<p>Fol. 1 originally belonged to another MS.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Some leaves had been damaged and were later restored; some of the leaves bear stains.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1">
									<p>Uniform layout</p>
									<p>Numerous marginal notes.</p>
									<p>Maniculae (e.g. on folios 8v, 43v, 69v, 125r).</p>
									<p>Hair and flesh side are distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Pricking and ruling is often visible.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc>
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script of the 13th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Cat paw prints on fols. 60v-61r.</p>
							<p>Paper slip with Latin note about the content of the MS.</p>
						></additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM/BL in-house binding.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Avicenna. Canon. Bk. III. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Harleian MS. 5707.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
